## 4. The Disk I/O Subsystem (Dual-CSR)

Since both the Composite Graph and the Reverse Index are on disk, the background sweep worker needs an efficient way to read them without thrashing the NVMe.

```rust
use std::fs::File;
use std::os::unix::fs::FileExt;

/// Dual-CSR for Disk-Backed Graphs.
/// The sweep worker reads the Reverse Index to find affected composites,
/// then reads the Composite Graph to resolve the null-rebinds.
pub struct DiskGraphs {
    reverse_csr: File,   // 4 GB
    graph_csr: File,     // 12 GB
    offsets: Vec<u64>,   // 80 MB (RAM)
}

impl DiskGraphs {
    /// Fetches all triples involving a deleted atom.
    /// Called ONLY by the background sweep worker.
    pub fn fetch_affected_triples(&self, atom_id: u32) -> std::io::Result<Vec<Triple>> {
        let start = self.offsets[atom_id as usize];
        let end = self.offsets[atom_id as usize + 1];
        let len = (end - start) as usize;
        if len == 0 { return Ok(Vec::new()); }

        // Read the composite IDs from the reverse CSR
        let mut rev_buf = vec![0u8; len * 4];
        self.reverse_csr.read_exact_at(&mut rev_buf, start)?;

        // Read the actual triples from the graph CSR
        let mut graph_buf = vec![0u8; len * 12];
        self.graph_csr.read_exact_at(&mut graph_buf, start * 3)?; // 12/4 = 3x offset

        Ok(graph_buf.chunks_exact(12).map(|c| Triple::from_bytes(c)).collect())
    }
}
```

